Company Profile
Fuding rubber group was established in 2007, our group was founded based on the rubber foaming technology, started with mouse pads business, after more than ten years of development, gradually expand the Yoga mat, mat, Kitchen mat & Cup mat and so on product category, and realize from foam rubber raw materials, combine, engraving, printing, overlock to final packaging the whole process of vertical integration of production line, already become China′s Top3 natural rubber mat manufacturer, Tier 1 mouse pad, yoga mat and household mat provider, our group planning in the next three years to achieve output over hundred million, export amount to tens of millions of dollars! At present, the group has nearly 200 employees, including Guizhou production base, Nanjing sales center and Dongguan logistics center, 2 amazon platforms, Aliexpress and 1688 and other sales platforms. Meanwhile, the group participated in the Canton fair, Hong Kong exhibition and Taiwan exhibition in 2019. Our products are made of natural rubber foam, which is environmentally friendly, safe and non-toxic, and deeply loved by international customers. Therefore, our products are sold in more than 50 countries and regions all over the world. Moreover, we have some famous business partner as Logitech, Paul Frank, Korea Line, Japan Hello Kitty and Thailand 7-11. In 2020, we will open more Made-in-China stores, and plan to attend landmark exhibitions or visit key customers in major world markets such as Germany, the United States, South Korea, Japan, the United Kingdom and India. Fuding Group know technology at the same time, the patent and certification to the important role of enterprise core competitiveness, with ISO9001, RoHS, Reach, SGS, EN71 and IC, and other well-known international certification, and at the same time has more than 20 products technical patents, in the future we will continue to increase investment in these areas, our production capacity, team, platform, customers and all aspects of development, 3 years off of the Fuding rubber group plans to lay a solid foundation!

Man identified in deadly Ellsworth car crash
by: Mike Smith
Posted: Jul 6, 2021 / 02:41 PM CDT
Updated: Jul 6, 2021 / 03:27 PM CDT
by: Mike Smith
Posted: Jul 6, 2021 / 02:41 PM CDT
Updated: Jul 6, 2021 / 03:27 PM CDT
ELLSWORTH, Ill. (WMBD) — The McLean County Coroner has identified the man who died in a car crash near North and East St. in Ellsworth Monday.
Coroner Kathy Yoder said 40-year-old Daniel E. Engler of Bloomington was pronounced deceased at 7:30 p.m. Monday after sustaining positional asphyxia and blunt injuries of his neck.
Initial reports show Engler lost control of his vehicle on a gravel roadway, left the road, and overturned his vehicle.
A passenger of the vehicle was injured in the crash and was taken to a local hospital. There has not been an update on their condition since Monday.
The crash is being investigated by the McLean County Coroner’s Office and the McLean County Sheriff’s Department.
